HEADWORD: Throwing
<hw>Throw"ing</hw>, <def><pos>a. & n.</pos> from <er>Throw</er>,
<pos>v.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Throwing engine</b></col>, <col><b>Throwing
mill</b></col>, <col><b>Throwing table</b></col>, <it>or</it>
<col><b>Throwing wheel</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Pottery)</fld>, <cd>a
machine on which earthenware is first rudely shaped by the hand of the
potter from a mass of clay revolving rapidly on a disk or table carried
by a vertical spindle; a potter's wheel.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

